id: writing-standards-policy
severity: critical
description: "Writing standards: no gray text, no em-dashes, no double-hyphen separators, no Oxford commas"
guard: "NO AGENT MAY OUTPUT LOW-CONTRAST TEXT, EM-DASHES, OR DOUBLE-HYPHENS. Minimum contrast for all text. Em-dash and en-dash characters are forbidden. Double-hyphens used as word separators are forbidden."
rules:
  - All text must use minimum readable contrast - no faint or hard-to-read colors
  - Em-dash (U+2014) and en-dash (U+2013) characters are FORBIDDEN in all output
  - Double-hyphens as word separators are FORBIDDEN - use single hyphen
  - Oxford commas are FORBIDDEN - no comma before 'and' or 'or' in lists
  - CSS custom properties and CLI flags with double-hyphens are exempt
